title: Dyer's Record Book, 1874–76
inscribed: Front cover: Delaines Book D, 1874, Old Pacific Print Works
creditline: Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts
description: Notebook with handwritten formulas for dyestuffs to be used for printing textiles. Contains 160 samples in various designs.

tombstone.epitaph: Dyer's Record Book, 1874–76. Medium: cardboard, paper, printed samples. Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts. 1945-55-18.
